          h2 Purposes of the Trek
          p A pioneer trek is a special opportunity for youth to have spiritual experiences where they gain a deeper appreciation for pioneers who forged a path before them. It is a type of youth conference where youth can grow their testimonies, gain appreciation for one&#8217;s ancestors and the pioneers, increase their self worth by preparing spiritually and physically and knowing they can accomplish hard things, gain new friends and build stronger peer relationships in a safe but challenging setting (see <a href="https://www.lds.org/handbook/handbook-2-administering-the-church/activities?lang=eng#134">Handbook 2 13.4</a> and <a href="https://www.lds.org/bc/content/ldsorg/content/english/pdf/service/aaronic-priesthood/scouting/handcart-trek-guidelines.pdf?lang=eng">Church Youth Handcart Trek Guidelines</a>).
